ol.li: Trie Principle: Hierarchical tables are a "Radix Trie". Unmapped virtual ranges are NULL pointers, pruning subtrees.
The 4MB Threshold: Each Page Directory Entry (PDE) controls 4MB. Sparsity across 4MB boundaries determines L2 allocation.
Worst Case Cost: In the pathological case (1 page per 4MB), M3 is slightly larger (100.1%) due to the 4KB Directory overhead.
Production Reality: Real processes are sparse. Savings of >99% are standard for typical application address spaces.
